    <div class="container">
        <p>Bioluminescence is the production and emission of light by living organisms. It is a widespread phenomenon in the ocean, where it is primarily produced by marine organisms such as jellyfish, plankton, and certain species of fish.</p>
        
        <div class="image-container">
